US: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It's funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the dumbest.
When he finally revealed his expected Afghan approach, it was demonstrated that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is used several times the words "equal as in Iraq", but it also did not hesitate to use the title of the Bush declaration of January 2007 for its own statement: "A new way forward".
It was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision and with catastrophic consequences".
The following months, however, demonstrated that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful one, so that nothing of Iraq is spoken today in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however, objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than he might have expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will be repeated.
The camp captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan General Operation Stanley McCristal. He, despite the traditional subordinate relations, subjected the undecided gunmen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He asked for 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened, so at least he tricked the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he himself previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's whole strategy seems to be its goal, to start withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to finish this procedure in three years. Obama's entire doctrine generated more questions than the answers it offered.
Many doubt that the increase yields the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is made.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, if they are accustomed to changing the head each day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. Following it will remain patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even to establish a state that is "capable of action", a minimum goal of the whole operation, seems very real.
Obama's strategy horizon is shocked by his volunteerism.
For the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the soldiers sent to the war to "come home soon," will perform some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, as the Taliban will view it as an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The latest NATO summit has shown that Europeans are increasingly less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of developments in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions do not have any effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek answers precisely when, according to Obama, America initiates the triumphal withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic reversal to the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for the presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
