Cars with historical value can be discharged even though they have been lowered after some tedious actions.
Four-step workshop budget
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audatex company ensures that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the replacement, create the budget and generate the budget.
The ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially in order to convince older professionals that, to a greater or lesser extent, they are more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 cars, 109 totterrenos, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with internet connection.
Once the model has been identified to be repaired by its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the workforce, charges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working time.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is EUR 350 per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently the Audatex company is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inside face.
